race.description: Ladbrokes Spring Hosted Pots Mdn Plate
race.comment: PRONOUNCED (3) is a gelding by Ghaiyyath on debut for the Price & Kent Jnr yard. He's jumped out quite well and the stable are very good with their newcomers. This looks a winnable affair and he can run well first time of asking. ROULETTE KING (4) was close up in a bunched finish on debut at Geelong over 1140m. Can only improve off that and draws well here. MELEYS (8) ran a strong race on debut at Echuca over 1300m to get within a nose. Query on how far back she gets here but clearly looks to have the ability to figure. TISSEYRE (10) was no match for the winner but held down second nicely on debut at Moe with improvement to come. BONUS SEASON (7) was in the market on debut and could be a sharp improver for the top yard.
